# Plan: Make schemas the single source of truth (post-Zod cleanup)

## Context

The Zod migration landed but left three friction points:
1. `AgentId` + `AGENT_IDS` are still defined in `types.ts` and mirrored in `schemas/manifest.ts` — the schema uses `superRefine + .transform(v => v as AgentId)` as a workaround instead of `z.enum()` which would make the type derivation direct.
2. `Manifest`/`SkillEntry` in `types.ts` and `Registry`/`RegistryEntry` in `ownership.ts` are hand-maintained interfaces parallel to the schemas, forcing `as Manifest` and `as Registry` casts at the call sites.
3. `index.ts` agent list parsing still splits, loops, calls `validate()`, and casts `ids as AgentId[]` — three separate steps that could be collapsed into one typed `.map()`.
4. `formatPath` is local to `manifest.ts`; if any future config file adopts this Zod-based pattern, it will copy the helper.

Goal: remove all redundant type definitions, casts, and the loop/cast in `index.ts` by deriving everything from the schemas.

---

## Changes

### 1. `src/schemas/manifest.ts` — `z.enum()` + export derived types

Move `AGENT_IDS` here (remove from `types.ts`) and switch `AgentIdSchema` to `z.enum()`, which makes `AgentId` a direct output type with no `transform` or cast:

```ts
const AGENT_IDS = [
  "claude-code", "codex", "gemini-cli",
  "antigravity", "opencode", "github-copilot",
] as const;

export { AGENT_IDS };

export const AgentIdSchema = z.enum(AGENT_IDS);
export type AgentId = z.output<typeof AgentIdSchema>;
export type SkillEntry = z.infer<typeof SkillEntrySchema>;
export type Manifest = z.infer<typeof ManifestSchema>;
```

Remove the `import type { AgentId }` and `import { AGENT_IDS }` from `types.ts` — no longer needed.

The `z.enum()` error message for an invalid value will be Zod's default `"Invalid option: '...' ..."`. This breaks the test `/unknown agent "unknown-agent"/`. Fix in `manifest.ts`'s error mapper (see below).

### 2. `src/schemas/registry.ts` — export derived types

```ts
export type RegistryEntry = z.infer<typeof RegistryEntrySchema>;
export type Registry = z.infer<typeof RegistrySchema>;
```

### 3. `src/schemas/errors.ts` (new) — shared path formatter

Extract `formatPath` from `manifest.ts` into a shared module:

```ts
export function formatZodPath(path: (string | number)[]): string {
  if (path.length === 0) return "";
  return `${path.map((seg, i) => {
    if (typeof seg === "number") return `[${seg}]`;
    return i === 0 ? seg : `.${seg}`;
  }).join("")} `;
}
```

### 4. `src/types.ts` — re-export from schemas

Remove `AgentId`, `AGENT_IDS`, `Manifest`, `SkillEntry` definitions; re-export them so all existing importers remain unchanged:

```ts
export type { AgentId, Manifest, SkillEntry } from "./schemas/manifest.ts";
export { AGENT_IDS } from "./schemas/manifest.ts";
// Everything else (AgentPaths, Confidence, AgentConfig, DeployAction, etc.) stays
```

### 5. `src/config/manifest.ts` — remove local `formatPath`, handle enum error

- Remove `formatPath` (use `formatZodPath` from `schemas/errors.ts`)
- Remove `import type { Manifest }` (no longer needed; type flows from `safeParse`)
- Add enum error handling so the test `/unknown agent "unknown-agent"/` keeps passing:

```ts
import { formatZodPath } from "../schemas/errors.ts";
import { AGENT_IDS } from "../types.ts";

// in validateManifest:
const issue = result.error.issues[0];
const path = issue.path as (string | number)[];

// top-level "skills" missing/wrong type
if (path.length === 1 && path[0] === "skills") {
  throw new UserError("MANIFEST_INVALID", `${filePath}: "skills" must be an array`);
}

// enum failure on agent ID
if (issue.code === "invalid_enum_value" && typeof issue.received === "string") {
  const prefix = formatZodPath(path);
  throw new UserError(
    "MANIFEST_INVALID",
    `${filePath}: ${prefix}unknown agent "${issue.received}". Valid agents: ${AGENT_IDS.join(", ")}`,
  );
}

const prefix = formatZodPath(path);
throw new UserError("MANIFEST_INVALID", `${filePath}: ${prefix}${issue.message}`);
```

The `return result.data as Manifest` cast becomes `return result.data` since `z.infer<typeof ManifestSchema>` now equals `Manifest`.

### 6. `src/core/ownership.ts` — remove hand-maintained interfaces

Remove the `RegistryEntry` interface and `Registry` interface; import derived types from schemas:

```ts
import type { Registry, RegistryEntry } from "../schemas/registry.ts";
```

Remove `AgentId` import (it flows through `RegistryEntry` from the schema now).
The `result.data as Registry` cast disappears.

`RegistryEntry` is exported from `ownership.ts` today. Change to re-export from schemas:
```ts
export type { RegistryEntry } from "../schemas/registry.ts";
```

### 7. `src/index.ts` — collapse split+loop+cast into one `.map()`

```ts
agents = values.agents
  .split(",")
  .map((s) => s.trim())
  .map((id) => {
    const r = AgentIdSchema.safeParse(id);
    if (!r.success) {
      throw new UserError(
        "INVALID_ARGS",
        `Unknown agent: "${id}". Valid agents: ${AGENT_IDS.join(", ")}`,
      );
    }
    return r.data;  // AgentId — no cast
  });
```

Remove the `validate` import from `schemas/validate.ts` (no longer needed in `index.ts`).

---

## Critical Files

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `src/schemas/manifest.ts` | Move `AGENT_IDS` here; switch to `z.enum()`; export derived types |
| `src/schemas/registry.ts` | Export derived types |
| `src/schemas/errors.ts` | New — `formatZodPath` helper |
| `src/types.ts` | Re-export `AgentId`, `AGENT_IDS`, `Manifest`, `SkillEntry` from schemas |
| `src/config/manifest.ts` | Use `formatZodPath`; handle `invalid_enum_value`; remove `as Manifest` cast |
| `src/core/ownership.ts` | Remove hand interfaces; import types from schemas; remove `as Registry` cast |
| `src/index.ts` | Collapse agent list parsing to typed `.map()`; remove `validate` import |

---

## Verification

1. `npm run typecheck` — no casts, derived types must satisfy all call sites
2. `npm test` — all 94 tests pass, especially `test/manifest.test.ts` (`unknown agent "..."` and `"skills" must be an array` substrings)
3. `npm run lint && npm run fmt`
4. Smoke: `node src/index.ts limbo --dry-run`

